Consumer Address verification includes a powerful address verification tool that helps minimize identity fraud by comparing an applicant's personal identification information against public record databases to flag inconsistencies. Consumer address verification also provides a fast and efficient method for complying with Section 326 of the USA Patriot Act and FACTA Red Flag Rules.

This address verification API makes it possible to authenticate new customers address information before they open an account. Consumer address verification can also be used to validate existing customers address information. 

Who is it for: Developers creating or integrating apps that need an address authentication service.

How is it used: Employ this API to create or integrate address verification applications with public record databases to authenticate a customers address information. 

Begin the integration with following address verification service domain in API Explorer:

Consumer Address verification
